{"name":"Praetorian, Charger and Queen Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"xfkdUl7SK5rG00td","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Call the Guard: </b> The enormous Xenomorph lets out a shrill cry for help, calling D6 Sentries (for the Queen) or Soldiers (for the Praetorian or Charger) to its defense. They reach the zone the following Round, then draw initiative and can act.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qJLhRh8om2P5bDzv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Charge: </b> Charger only (re-roll for Praetorian or Queen). The target must make a MOBILITY roll (no action) or be crushed, being immediately Broken and suffering a random critical injury. Even if the victim makes the roll, they fall down and gain +1 STRESS LEVEL.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7lQItz6wD0IpTLZp","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Beastly Bite: </b> The Xenomorph takes a huge bite from its victim. The attack is rolled with ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes any damage, it inflicts critical injury #61 even if the victim isn’t Broken, triggering a Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DFzEWXMPEiQ3ElY3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Crushing Blow: </b> The Xenomorph brings its entire weight down on the poor victim, who must make a MOBILITY roll at –2 (no action) or be crushed, immediately suffering three critical injuries (roll three times on the critical injury table and apply all three results, regardless of whether or not the victim is Broken). The victim is knocked to the ground and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"gOuokbDksvTF3iqJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Tail Spike: </b> The tail impales the victim with terrible force. Roll for the attack using ten Base Dice (fourteen for a Queen), Damage 1. The attack is armor piercing. If the attack causes any damage it automatically triggers critical injury #66, killing them outright.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RUKe5pZbanVpCFYV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Headbite: </b> The Xenomorph opens its mouth wide and the inner jaws lash out. The attack uses ten Base Dice, Damage 2. If it causes any damage the victim immediately suffers critical injury #64, killing them in one dreadful blow.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"7Hi5YIovRCn8QD75"}
{"name":"Soldier and Sentry Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"r2VBvHpocF38kClX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Assessing the Threat: </b> The Xenomorph pauses, hissing quietly but all the more threatening for that. It looks like it’s thinking, or maybe giving silent orders to unseen companions. Everyone within MEDIUM range gets +1 STRESS LEVEL.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0oPX3AdNHT7WGqit","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>One for All: </b> The Xeno leaps at the largest group of enemies and roars a challenge, sweeping its arms, legs and tail through their ranks. All targets within SHORT range must succeed at a MOBILITY roll or be knocked off their feet, taking one point of damage. All the targets must make immediate Panic Rolls.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"09uoHYP92veSGSFT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>All-Out Attack: /b&gt; The Xenomorph launches into a wild attack, throwing every claw, fang and its pointed tail at its victim. It attacks with twelve Base Dice, Damage 2, and the attack is armor piercing.</b>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"4vlxf1tj14k68e66","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Capture for the Hive: </b> The Xenomorph attacks with its venom-spiked tail, with twelve Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes any damage, the Xeno pulls its punch so only one point of damage is inflicted, and the paralyzing venom takes effect. The victim must make a STAMINA roll—the number of Success's rolled is the number of Rounds they can stay up, then they fall unconscious for one Shift. The paralysis can be removed with a shot of adrenaline (a MEDICAL AID roll using a Medkit), but otherwise the Xeno will capture them for the egg chamber.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"adzL5kVlHxX6XsoG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Die for the Queen: </b>The Xenomorph, desperate to protect its hive and Queen, leaps towards an enemy, eviscerating itself as it does so. Its acid blood showers everywhere: all targets within SHORT range of the Xeno suffer an immediate acid splash attack of twelve Base Dice. The Xeno dies, squealing.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"lkXu8GxNRrHixmr7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Headbite: </b> The Xenomorph opens its outer jaws wide, and the deadly inner jaws lean out, gnashing in anticipation before snapping forwards. The attack is rolled with ten Base Dice, Damage 2. If it causes any damage it automatically inflicts critical injury #64, killing the victim in one dreadful blow.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"ETyiYy2oaoYaOazJ"}
{"name":"Chestburster Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"DI0ToFQYzfEpYhnW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Escape: </b> With a snarl the Chestburster flees, moving two zones away in one action, into the nearest vent, sewer or duct if possible. As soon as the PC's lose line of sight the Chestburster has escaped. Stealth mode ensues as the Chestburster tries to hide and grow.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Ki3ksWdttCGBqR0X","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Terrorizing Hiss: </b> The Chest burster jumps towards a target, flashing its razor-sharp teeth and hissing malevolently. The target must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"00lBfemGMCb7znwU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Throat Bite: </b> The Chestburster squeals a high-pitched shriek and goes for the throat. Roll for the attack with eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes damage, it immediately inflicts critical injury #61 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5TkaMT4E3WajPB3s","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Leg Slash: </b> With a snarl the Chestburster slashes its target's leg, metallic teeth flashing in the light. Roll for the attack using six Base Dice, Damage 2. If the attack causes damage, it automatically inflicts critical injury #53 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"McoTpEmTsH1qMUgN"}
{"name":"Stalker, Scout and Drone Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"ulwSTrcOU4OS1KlN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Hypnotizing Gaze: </b> The Xenomorph, eyeless as it may seem, stares deeply into the soul of its victim. The victim is mesmerized by the dread beauty of such a beast. They stand in awe of what nature, or god, or the devil has created, get +1 STRESS LEVEL and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tEqWkEEHbK7E0eHR","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Playing With Its Prey</b> The Xeno attacks, but not to kill. The target is knocked to the ground and drops all hand-held items, but otherwise takes no damage. The Xenomorph stands over them, taunting its prey to run so the game can go on. The victim gets +1 STRESS LEVEL and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8sqjdmFVj2PY5swb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Deadly Grab: </b> The beast launches through the air, grabbing its victim. It attacks with ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If it hits it immediately drags them into a neighboring zone, dumping them on the floor. The victim is prone, drops all hand-held items and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PjnUu6kmu6DDmNkU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Ready to Kill: </b> The Xenomorph grabs its victim, its inner jaws poised to strike. Roll for the attack with ten Base Dice. If it hits, the victim counts as grabbed (see page 93) and needs to make an opposed CLOSE COMBAT roll against ten Base Dice to break loose. The victim and all friendly characters in the same zone must make Panic Rolls. Unless the victim breaks free, the Xenomorph will use a HEADBITE attack against them on its next initiative. <br /><br /> <i>HEADBITE: The Xenomorph opens its outer jaws wide, and the deadly inner jaws lean out, gnashing in anticipation before snapping forwards. The attack has a strength of nine Base Dice, Damage 2. If it causes any damage it automatically inflicts critical injury #64, killing the victim in one dreadful blow. However, should the GM wish it, the victim remains just alive enough for the Xenomorph to initiate the ovomorphing process.</i>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"FnosZygCZZtno5FW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Capture for the Hive: </b> The Xenomorph attacks with its venom-spiked tail, with ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes any damage, the Xeno pulls its punch so only one point of damage is inflicted, and the paralyzing venom takes effect. The victim must make a STAMINA roll—the number of Success's rolled is the number of Rounds they can stay up, then they fall unconscious for one Shift. The paralysis can be removed with a shot of adrenaline (a MEDICAL AID roll using a Medkit).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"J9GMqRdv9mF3uuf5","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Headbite: </b> The Xenomorph opens its outer jaws wide, and the deadly inner jaws lean out, gnashing in anticipation before snapping forwards. The attack has a strength of nine Base Dice, Damage 2. If it causes any damage it automatically inflicts critical injury #64, killing the victim in one dreadful blow. However, should the GM wish it, the victim remains just alive enough for the Xenomorph to initiate the ovomorphing process.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"SLCOYdKLRGTE3Hlp"}
{"name":"Neomorphic Bloodburster Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"alien2","system":"alienrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.2","systemVersion":"0.1.5"}},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"t4Zd6RNvrwKTRYB7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Escape: </b>With a snarl, the Bloodburster flees, moving two zones away in a single action, into the nearest air duct if possible. As soon as the PCs lose line of sight, combat ends and stealth mode ensues. After D6 Turns, the Bloodburster grows into a Juvenile Neomorph and starts stalking the PCs. ","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"cFh9LndhMHs4tY1A","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Terrifying Hiss: </b> The Bloodburster jumps onto the victim, showing its razor-sharp teeth andhissing. The victim must make an immediate Panic Roll.  ","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"q9DDgxzaG12fMIns","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Leg Bite: </b> With a snarl, the Bloodburster bites the victim’s leg. Roll for the attack using six Base Dice, Damage 2. If the attack causes damage, it automatically inflicts critical injury  #53 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll. ","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"shYPbiSjp6LiLRQ8","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Throat Bite: </b> The Bloodburster bites the victim’s throat. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes damage, it automatically inflicts critical injury #61 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll.  ","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"YVTBrEraNP7CDUtc"}
{"name":"Sub Table Facehugger Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"Sub RollTable for \"4 Tail Grapple\" Facehugger Attacks","results":[{"_id":"WBItoCQpT5fPN4PJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The Facehugger leaps and catches its victim from behind, its tail whipping violently. The target's legs are caught and they fall prone-make a Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fEr9ue5xhbySDXe3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The Facehugger leaps and catches its victim from behind, its tail whipping violently. The victim's arms get hopelessly tangled in the beast's tail-they cannot use any held items and must make a Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"D2s2E1QN6SzOTFh3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The Facehugger leaps and catches its victim from behind, its tail whipping violently. The Facehugger wraps its tail around the target's neck, choking them-they suffer the effects of Drowning and must make a Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"YqYbuQLiLG1WErlW"}
{"name":"Lion Worm Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"mnt27YEsJZd0D19n","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Intimidating Display: </b> The Lion Worm rears up, its golden cilia flowing in threatening patterns. But it’s a bluff. The expert predator has seen a problem and is using an aggressive display to cover a tactical retreat (which it makes on its next action). All PCs within SHORT range must make a Panic Roll. But the Lion Worm is not giving up the hunt: when it retreats, stealth mode resumes with the Lion Worm still hunting the PCs. When it makes its next attack, it gets a +1 to its roll on this table (to a maximum of 6).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"aVCQcPFCTZofIwpZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Play With Its Prey: </b> The Lion Worm attacks but for fun, rather than to kill. Roll for the attack with eight Base Dice. If the attack hits, the target is knocked to the ground and drops all hand-held items, but is otherwise unharmed. The Worm rears over them, wishing for its prey to run before it attacks again. The victim must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RWKs0pId7DoCskjN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Acrid Pheramones: </b> The Lion Worm releases a huge dump of pheromones into the air. They are so pungent that anyone near the creature starts to cough and all PCs within SHORT range must make a STAMINA roll. If unsuccessful they are stunned and lose their next slow action.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"NbBVGZsbf1vUSm3a","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Feral Rage: </b> The beast attacks, throwing everything at its victim, with ten Base Dice, Damage 2. If it causes any damage, its insatiable desire to kill allows it to immediately make a second attack as a free action, with the same number of Base Dice and Damage rating.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"z2s4eyEgUKgbFps1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Crippling Attack: </b> The Lion Worm attacks to incapacitate its target, either to eat later or get enough space to escape a bad situation. It goes for a crippling blow, making an attack with eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If it does any damage it automatically inflicts critical injury #56, even if the victim isn’t Broken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"UgKtDxhQIZzWJpDv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Death Roll: </b> The Lion Worm goes full out for the kill, grasping its target and wrapping it in a vicious death roll. Roll for the attack with ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack hits, the victim is grappled as well as disorientated and loses their next slow action. On its next action, the Lion Worm will squeeze the victim, attacking with ten Base Dice, Damage 1 again.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"bYfzXP4oQeA505BO"}
{"name":"Harvester Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"fRi81O2SQ5xjcqJv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Sonar Sweep: </b> The Harvester takes in its surroundings by singing out a quick sonar pulse. Add one to the next roll on this table (for a maximum of 6). All PCs at up to LONG range are affected by the high-pitched squeal and get +1 STRESS LEVEL.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"h3VibiiDKBmA8bWc","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Sonar Pulse: </b> The Harvester uses its sonar as a weapon. Everyone within SHORT range gets blasted by the ultra-sonic burst and must make a STAMINA roll (no action) or be stunned and lose their next action. Those who are not stunned must make a Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"HMEejwwPqg1vr9Kl","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Charge: </b> The cornered Harvester rushes the player who it deems to be the biggest threat. It makes a manic charge against them, and all those in that direction, as its charge crosses into the next zone. All targets must make a MOBILITY roll (no action) to get out of the way. Anyone who fails suffers an attack rolled with ten Base Dice, Damage 1, and is knocked prone.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"1ip92jzoUeKKI35R","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Stampede: </b> The Harvester goes berserk, like a bucking bronco, and flails around in a maddened frenzy. All targets within SHORT range suffer a crushing attack of six Base Dice, Damage 2, and are knocked prone if hit.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"sOVrlldc6EDH0dIg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Burrowing Claws: </b> The beast’s claws are almost as bad as its maw, and it leaps on a poor victim. They suffer an attack with ten Base Dice, Damage 2.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hMwxmyYXIUYojWxc","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Pulverize: </b> The victim is dragged into the beast’s dreadful meat-grinder of a mouth. They get to make a last-ditch opposed CLOSE COMBAT roll against eight Base Dice (no action), to dodge that dreadful fate. If they fail the roll they die, their body mercilessly minced, their agonized screams ringing in the ears of their friends until the day they die. All who witness this receive +1 STRESS LEVEL and must make a Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"bvR4MIs6gxAozkQU"}
{"name":"Facehugger Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"Attacks for a Facehugger","results":[{"_id":"ENB2ekEIIM4n5Eev","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Skittering Menace:</b> The Facehugger has chosen its host and they know it is coming for them! It skitters forward, single-minded and horrifyingly spider-like. The victim suffers +1 Stress Level and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0uwPCeZGjKWmehGe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Tail Lash: </b>The little monster comes for its target, lashing out with its wicked tail. It attacks with five Base Dice, Damage 1. (The Royal Facehugger uses six Base Dice, base Damage 2). Aside from any damage the victim get +1 Stress Level","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"I9DkeGjKHNqEMPEQ","flags":{},"type":1,"text":"Sub Table Facehugger Attacks","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","collection":"RollTable","resultId":"3wpiJT3XD4hWgf7i","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RYWx8j1tL5AV9mGG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Face Grapple:</b> The Facehugger leaps at its victim. Make an opposed roll with six Base Dice against the target's Close Combat skill (not counting as an action for the victim): <br /> <br /> If the victim wins they throw the beast to the floor, but it's not finished with them yet and attacks the same target again on its next initiative.<br /> <br />If the Facehugger wins, the target will suffer the Final Embrace on the Facehugger's next Initiative. <br /> <br /> <i>The Final Embrace: The Facehugger gets to its victim, its acid making short work of any helmet or respirator in the way. Roll for the attack with six Base Dice. If it gets one or more Success's, the poor victim is facehugged and immediately Broken. Their last sensations are horrible, yet strangely loving: a firm but gentle caress around their head; a smothering sensation followed by a warm burst of oxygen-rich air filling their lungs; a deep sensation of slow-motion falling; it's okay to fall asleep...</i>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"iOpBOVcEtwmRj3Kr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>The Final Embrace: </b> The Facehugger gets to its victim, its acid making short work of any helmet or respirator in the way. Roll for the attack with six Base Dice. If it gets one or more Success's, the poor victim is facehugged and immediately Broken. Their last sensations are horrible, yet strangely loving: a firm but gentle caress around their head; a smothering sensation followed by a warm burst of oxygen-rich air filling their lungs; a deep sensation of slow-motion falling; it's okay to fall asleep...","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"clDG4Q7AF4p3TwJT"}
{"name":"Neomorph Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"38QQwtGYd2wiwzjb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Terrifying Hiss:</b> The Neomorph leans in close to the victim, showing its razor-sharp teeth and hissing. The victim must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"cjcjJqJgOvFHhrnQ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Tail Slash:</b> The Neomorph pivots, slashing its victim with its sharp tail. The victim is attacked using ten Base Dice, Damage +2. The attack is armor piercing, halving any Armor Rating.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"IffRPYzBLoPjSYvD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Deadly Grab:</b> The Neomorph jumpas at its victim, grabbing it and dragging it away. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If it hits, the Neomorph immediately drags the victim into the next zone (Medium range) before releasing it. The victim falls prone, drops any hand-held items, and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"KeNesVkGinA8rqG9","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Leaping Attack:</b> The Neomorph jumps at the victim. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack is successful, the victim is thrown to the ground and must make an immediate Panic Roll, and the Neomorph immediately performs an extra attack with ten Base Dice, Damage 2 (does not count aas an action). The extra attack cannot be blocked.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"EbbBWfmwxnrGN7hY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Throat Bite: </b> The Neomorph bites the victim's throat. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes damage, it automatically inflicts critical injury #61 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RR9OFjsh7eyN6wn2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Tail Spike:</b> The Neomorph impales the victim with its razor-sharp tail. Roll for the attack using seven Base Dice, Damage 1. The attack is armor piercing, halving any Armor Rating. If the attack causes damage, it automatically triggers critical injury #66 (even if the victim is not Broken), killing the victim outright.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"gdzqo3GLfoVFgaaM"}
{"name":"Sub Table Critical Injuries on Xenomorphs","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"Sub Roll table for \"3 Desperate Action\" on Critical Injuries on Xenomorphs","results":[{"_id":"TrzTuZKEmsZpBHx8","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Desperate Action:</b> The Xenomorph is severely wounded and cries out in alien fury. It immediately gets to perform a fast and a slow action, outside of the normal turn order. It tries to escape (if it succeeds it regains half its Health).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"eqJW9GsJEDKEfjl7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Desperate Action:</b> The Xenomorph is severely wounded and cries out in alien fury. It immediately gets to perform a fast and a slow action, outside of the normal turn order. It instantly attacks the closest opponent. If it fails to inflict any damage, the creature dies. If it succeeds, it regains one point of Health.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"lNSAixCW69Gbi3vF"}
{"name":"Scorpionid Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"ylflRaA2QSkpR0Dr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Retreat: </b> The Scorpionid isn’t stupid and won’t fight unless there’s a good reason to. On this occasion it decides to flee the fight as quickly as possible.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rQjXBpCasvkylX7Q","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Pinned Down: </b> The Scorpionid uses its powerful pincers to pin down its target. Roll for the attack using ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack hits, the target is knocked prone, drops any hand-held items and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"zrfbEoOuyXkpEm7R","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Pincer Grab: </b> The creature tries to seize its victim in its enormous claws, quivering with the anticipation of a quick strike with its huge tail. Roll for the attack with eight Base dice, Damage 1. If the attack hits, the victim is grappled (see page 93) and must make an opposed roll for CLOSE COMBAT against eight Base Dice to break loose. If the Scorpionid retains its grasp, it will automatically make a TAIL STRIKE (below) attack against the victim on its next initiative. If this attack hits underwater the Scorpionid will drag the victim deeper and one zone away from the group, causing them to also suffer the effects of drowning. <br /><br /><i>Tail Strike: The Scorpionid swings its terrible tail forward with deadly purpose. It attacks with ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If it inflicts any damage it poisons the victim with a deadly venom, counting as a disease with a Virulence rating of 9 (see page 109).</i>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"dPgUz1cCMC4Jd1Hy","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Flailing Strike: </b> The Scorpionid’s pincer swipes at its target. Roll for the attack with eight Base dice, Damage 1. If the attack hits, the Scorpionid flings the victim into the next zone, causing an immediate critical injury (regardless if the victim is Broken). The victim is left prone and drops any hand-held items.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WwKTVTRLaZzVydmL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Tail Strike: </b> The Scorpionid swings its terrible tail forward with deadly purpose. It attacks with ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If it inflicts any damage it poisons the victim with a deadly venom, counting as a disease with a Virulence rating of 9 (see page 109).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9sBfhBPVBB2lA2LK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Immobilize: </b> The Scorpionid wants to escape, but to do so it needs to take its attackers out of the fight. It lunges for its victim’s legs with its huge claws, making an attack with eight Base Dice, Damage 2. If it does any damage, the victim immediately suffers critical injury #35, whether or not they are Broken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"xGG8o2i8im1dUoHL"}
{"name":"Swarm Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"zhX1qJxLmSnJj9r1":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"Nnl8fM1YgBW3hGyS","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Consume: </b> The Swarm consumes everything in its path, and this place is rich in food. The Swarm’s Health is restored by 2 points, making it harder to drive off.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"XhczOQeVhKay4OYq","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Pheromones: </b> The Swarm is getting increasingly agitated and more and more pheromones are being released into the air. The Swarm’s next roll on this table gets +1. This effect is cumulative.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5PQB7jbLT6tWSqYg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Suffocating Swarm: </b> The swarming creatures are everywhere: the air is thick with them. They are in the victims’ eyes, ears and mouths, and it is almost impossible to breathe. Everyone inside the Swarm area must make a STAMINA roll. Failure means the victim cannot act during the next Round, and the Swarm will perform a STRIPPED TO THE BONE attack against the victim as its next action. <br /><br /><i>Stripped to the Bone: The Swarm focuses on one target, and that victim takes an attack rolled with eight Base Dice, Damage 1. Armor is halved (rounded down) as the creatures squirm underneath it. If the attack inflicts any damage the Swarm has ravaged the victim and they suffer a critical injury, even if not Broken. Each Round thereafter one of the Swarm’s actions is automatically to attack this target again with this attack, on the Swarm’s next initiative. This will continue until the victim is stripped to the bone, rescued, or the Swarm is driven off.</i>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PJBDVd8GZWxBL5EB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Desperate Hunger: </b> The Swarm is so hungry it will eat anything, and right now the polymers and compounds in the players’ armor look good. Everyone within the Swarm wearing armor suffers an attack rolled with eight Base Dice, Damage 1. Any damage is immediately subtracted from the Armor Rating. Those not wearing armor find their clothes have been shredded, but the attack does not inflict any damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"3ylidOEEHwA8iphP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Feeding Frenzy: </b> The Swarm is hungry and tries to eat anything it can envelope. All characters inside the Swarm suffer an attack rolled with six Base Dice, Damage 1. Armor is halved (rounded down) as the creatures look for ways to slip past it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0ayY3rnlVE9LClsR","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>Stripped to the Bone: </b> The Swarm focuses on one target, and that victim takes an attack rolled with eight Base Dice, Damage 1. Armor is halved (rounded down) as the creatures squirm underneath it. If the attack inflicts any damage the Swarm has ravaged the victim and they suffer a critical injury, even if not Broken. Each Round thereafter one of the Swarm’s actions is automatically to attack this target again with this attack, on the Swarm’s next initiative. This will continue until the victim is stripped to the bone, rescued, or the Swarm is driven off.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"yr4feqnILnkMmdfr"}
